info.description: Butt notch prob. orig. feature; arched shoulder on one side of bl./fg.junction - just hump on other side; stops dip from flanges - asym. and irreg. ; flattened fg. bases provide beginning of "V" enclosed depression on one face - virt. none on rev.; fairly crisp sep. angles; thin rounded/flattened fg. crests; fgs. skew to body e.g. fls. remains as cracks - one v. off central; deliberately dimpled bl. tips; some prob. hmks on sides; moulding irregularities on one sep. - prob. e.g. flaw; v. sl. flattening of top of fgs. - tending to tipping; 'hollow ground' e. bev. with suggestion of lesser bevel above; sl. bent and twisted along line of body - pres. dam.; edge intact and sharp.
